To add a timer to the word puzzle game, you can use JavaScript. You can create a countdown timer that specifies the amount of time each player is given to solve the puzzle. Here is an example of how you can add a timer to the word puzzle game:

1. Add a "timer" element to your HTML document where you want the countdown timer to be displayed.
```

```

2. In your JavaScript file, create a function that initializes and starts the timer.
```
function startTimer(duration, display) {
 var timer = duration, minutes, seconds;
 setInterval(function () {
 minutes = parseInt(timer / 60, 10);
 seconds = parseInt(timer % 60, 10);

 minutes = minutes < 10 ? "0" + minutes : minutes;
 seconds = seconds < 10 ? "0" + seconds : seconds;

 display.textContent = minutes + ":" + seconds;

 if (--timer < 0) {
 // timer ended, do something
 }
 }, 1000);
}
```

3. In the same JavaScript file, call the `startTimer` function and specify the amount of time you want the countdown timer to run for (in seconds) and the DOM element where you want it to be displayed.
```
var timerDisplay = document.querySelector('#timer');
var timeInSeconds = 120; // 2 minutes

startTimer(timeInSeconds, timerDisplay);
```

By following these steps, you should be able to add a countdown timer to the word puzzle game created using the modified XML data code.

