In Scala, you can handle errors when reading from a file by using the `try-catch` statement. Here's an example of how to read a line from a file:

```scala
import scala.io.Source

val file = Source.fromFile("file.txt")
try {
  val lines = file.getLines()
  println(lines)
} catch {
  case e: Exception => println(s"An error occurred: ${e.getMessage}")
}
```

In this example, if there is an exception (such as an error opening the file or reading it), the program will print the message "An error occurred:" followed by the exception message

