2. "taffeta skirts" - This is an example of consonance, where the "t" sound is repeated. It creates a sense of rustling and movement, which fits the description of palm trees swaying in the breeze.
3. "scent of jasmine" - This is an example of consonance, where the "s" sound is repeated. It creates a sense of sweetness and fragrance, which fits the description of a pleasant night.
The use of alliteration in this passage helps to create a sense of harmony and beauty in the setting. The repetition of sounds creates a musicality to the language, which adds to the overall mood of tranquility and peacefulness. It also helps to emphasize certain words and phrases, making them more memorable and impactful.

